  <text>
     <body>
     <div type="poem">
   <pb facs="10"/>
   <l>IF good to learne be thine entent,</l>
   <l>And not to plain of tyme yll spent:</l>
   <l>But so temploy thy present payne,</l>
   <l>As endles fruit may be thy gayne:</l>
   <l>This Treatise reade, and herein vew</l>
   <l>Al duties to thy Sauiour dew.</l>
   <l>For this doth teache for thy behoue,</l>
   <l>The lord thy god how thou shalt loue</l>
   <l>For loue of thee him selfe that gaue</l>
   <l>To death, frō death thy soule to saue.</l>
</div>
